  "title": "Aviation Technician (Aircraft Cabin Maintenance) #78073",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><ul><li>Industry/ Organization Type: Aviation/ Aircraft Components Repair</li><li>Position Title: <strong>Aviation Technician</strong></li><li>Working Location: Changi North</li><li>Working Hours: 5 Days, Monday – Friday (8am – 5.48pm)</li><li>Salary Package: <strong>Basic Salary + Performance Bonus</strong></li><li>Duration: Permanent</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Perform maintenance, repair, and refurbishment of aircraft cabin interiors, including seats, panels, carpets, and fittings.</li><li>Conduct inspections, troubleshooting, and rectification of cabin-related defects.</li><li>Assist in line and base maintenance tasks under supervision, including component replacements and system checks.</li><li>Support aircraft servicing activities and carry out minor structural repairs and modifications in accordance with approved maintenance data.</li><li>Maintain accurate records of maintenance activities, parts usage, and service reports.</li><li>Ensure compliance with CAAS regulations, company procedures, and safety protocols.</li><li>Collaborate with engineers, supervisors, and quality assurance teams to meet operational timelines.</li><li>Maintain cleanliness and organization of tools, equipment, and work areas.</li><li>Participate in continuous improvement initiatives and technical training programs.</li><li>Other duties as assigned.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>APPLY NOW!!!</strong></p><ul><li>At least Nitec in Aerospace, Engineering, or a related field.</li><li>Minimum 1-2 years of related work experience.</li><li>Preferably holds CAAS Air Law and Human Factors papers.</li><li>Must have hands-on experience in cabin interior repair.</li><li>Knowledgeable with aircraft systems and maintenance practices.</li><li></li></ul><p>Kindly apply through <strong>ANY </strong>of the following methods:</p><ul><li>Submit your application by clicking the <strong>APPLY </strong>button;</li><li>Email your resume to <a href=\"mailto:Job@anradus.com.sg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Job@anradus.com.sg</a>. Please indicate <strong>#78073 </strong>on the email subject.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Anradus Application Policy:</strong> We value each application and ensure every resume is reviewed. Our process is efficient, typically concluding within <strong>3 working days</strong>. If you do not receive communication from us within this timeframe, it's likely that your application has not been shortlisted by our client. In such cases, we recommend continuing your job search to maximize your opportunities.</p><p><br /><br /></p><p>Anradus Pte Ltd | EA License No. 20C0161 | Rachael Lee | EA Reg No.: R2093131</p>",
